Pivotal Bazaar for PCF enables the platform operator to provide app development team(s) with access to services running on
[Pivotal Container Service (PKS)](https://pivotal.io/platform/pivotal-container-service)
via the
[Cloud Foundry Marketplaces](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/devguide/services/index.html)
for consumption by PAS applications.


## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

PKS service integrations can take a lot of forms. Bazaar tackles two large classes of services:

* Installing a single Helm chart to a particular cluster (`shared-instance`).
* Provisioning services as needed by individual teams from the [Cloud Foundry Marketplaces](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/devguide/services/index.html) (`dedicated-instances`).
* Installing a cluster add-on, such as a observability or security tool.

In the shared-instance and add-on cases, bazaar helps by providing a consistent operator experience for installing a chart
into a particular cluster.

In the dedicated-instances case, Bazaar lets the operator offer an ISV or open source Helm charts to
[Pivotal Application Service](https://pivotal.io/platform/pivotal-application-service)
developers on demand. Developers who use the `cf create-service` command will, in realtime, provision a chart
to the service's backing cluster.


## <a id='features'></a>Key Features
Bazaar includes the following key features:

* A broker tile that provisions dedicated service instances into a PKS cluster.
* A CLI for downloading PKS integrations off Pivotal Network, managing broker dedicated-instance offerings,
  and installing a shared-instance into a cluster.


